| epics_path | string | No | Path to epics (AC traceability) | ./artifacts/outputs/product-definition/epics |
| dtr_path | string | No | Path to DTR (state observations) | ./artifacts/outputs/software-architecture/dtr |
| compliance_output_path | string | Yes | Output folder for COMPLIANCE-SPEC and COMPLIANCE-AUDIT | ./artifacts/outputs/product-delivery/architecture-compliance |
| story_scope | string | No | `all` \| `epic:<id>` \| `story:<ids>` | all |



**IMPORTANT — Structured Output Contract:**
After generating the COMPLIANCE-SPEC, you MUST write the following output
parameters so the orchestrating agent can read the verdict from session status:
- `compliance_status`: "PASSED" | "PARTIAL" | "FAILED"
  - PASSED  = all stories APPROVE
  - PARTIAL = some RETURN_TO_PRODUCT, zero INITIATE_ADR
  - FAILED  = any INITIATE_ADR
- `approve_count`, `return_to_product_count`, `initiate_adr_count`: counts per verdict
- `compliance_feedback`: one line per non-approved story:
  `[VERDICT] [STORY_ID] [GAP_CATEGORIES]`. Empty when PASSED.


