{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\context-pack\\arch-standards.md", "content": "1: # Architecture Standards\n2: # Star Wars Lego â€” Greenfield\n3: \n4: **Document Version:** 1.0\n5: \n6: ## 1. Software Architecture Principles\n7: \n8: ### 1.1 Single Page Application (SPA) Architecture\n9: The application follows a simplified Model-View-Controller (MVC) pattern implemented with Vue.js 2.x reactive framework. This architectural approach ensures:\n10: \n11: - **Separation of Concerns**: Clear distinction between data (Model), presentation (View), and user interactions (Controller)\n12: - **Reactive Data Flow**: Automatic UI updates when underlying data changes\n13: - **Component Reusability**: Modular Vue components for maintainability\n14: - **Local State Management**: Simplified state handling without complex backend integration\n15: \n16: ### 1.2 Component-Based Design\n17: - **Component Granularity**: Each major feature (Character Gallery, Search, Social Interactions) is implemented as a separate Vue component\n18: - **Props and Events**: Parent-child communication through explicit prop declarations and custom events\n19: - **Single Responsibility**: Each component has a focused, well-defined purpose\n20: - **State Encapsulation**: Component-scoped data to prevent unintended side effects\n21: \n22: ## 2. Frontend Architecture Standards\n23: \n24: ### 2.1 HTML5 Semantic Structure\n25: ```html\n26: <!DOCTYPE html>\n27: <html lang=\"pt-BR\">\n28: <head>\n29:   <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n30:   <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n31:   <title>Star Wars Lego - Interactive JavaScript Learning</title>\n32:   <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n33:   <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin>\n34: </head>\n35: <body>\n36:   <main id=\"app\" role=\"application\">\n37:     <!-- Vue.js application root -->\n38:   </main>\n39: </body>\n40: </html>\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ### 2.2 CSS3 Grid Layout Architecture\n44: ```css\n45: /* Main application container */\n46: .app-container {\n47:   display: grid;\n48:   grid-template-areas: \n49:     \"header\"\n50:     \"search\"", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 50, "returned_lines": 50, "has_more": true, "eof_reached": false, "truncated": false}}}
