{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\artifacts\\outputs\\product-delivery\\user-stories\\epics\\EPIC-01.md", "content": "1: ---\n2: epic_id: EPIC-01\n3: epic_title: Character Gallery Foundation\n4: session_id: product-delivery010307\n5: generated_at: 2026-07-03T16:35:00.000Z\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # EPIC-01: Character Gallery Foundation Stories\n9: \n10: ## ST-01: Character Grid Display\n11: \n12: **Tag:** [FE] Frontend/Web  \n13: **Priority:** Must Have  \n14: **Source FRs:** FR-01, FR-07  \n15: **Source NFRs:** NFR-03, NFR-04  \n16: **KPIs:** KPI-01, KPI-02  \n17: **Personas:** P-01, P-02, P-03\n18: \n19: **User Story:** As a beginner JavaScript student, I want to see 8 Star Wars Lego characters displayed in a responsive grid so I can explore visual DOM manipulation techniques.\n20: \n21: **Business Value:** Interactive character display enables hands-on JavaScript learning through visual DOM manipulation and component interaction patterns.\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n24: \n25: Given user accesses the application\n26: When the main page loads\n27: Then display 8 Star Wars Lego characters in a responsive grid layout\n28: And grid maintains minimum 820px viewport compatibility\n29: \n30: Given user hovers over a character card\n31: When cursor enters the character area\n32: Then show enhanced visual effects with smooth CSS transitions\n33: And transitions maintain 60fps performance\n34: And visual effects work across Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+\n35: \n36: Given user clicks on a character card\n37: When user selects character\n38: Then highlight selected character with visual feedback\n39: And show additional character information in detail panel\n40: And previously selected character loses highlight\n41: \n42: Given network connection is slow\n43: When loading character assets\n44: Then display loading indicators for each card\n45: And maintain responsive layout during load\n46: And show skeleton screens while content loads\n47: \n48: Given character data is unavailable\n49: When specific character fails to load\n50: Then display error state with retry option\n51: And maintain grid layout integrity\n52: And provide fallback visual representation\n53: \n54: **Definition of Done:**\n55: - Grid layout displays exactly 8 characters\n56: - Hover effects transition smoothly at 60fps\n57: - Character selection highlights correctly\n58: - Cross-browser compatibility verified\n59: - Responsive design adapts to 820px+ viewports\n60: - Loading states implemented for all character assets\n61: - Error handling covers API failures\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## ST-02: Character Data Management\n66: \n67: **Tag:** [BE] Backend/API  \n68: **Priority:** Must Have  \n69: **Source FRs:** FR-01  \n70: **Source NFRs:** NFR-01, NFR-02  \n71: **KPIs:** KPI-04, KPI-05  \n72: **Personas:** P-01, P-02\n73: \n74: **User Story:** As a web application, I need to manage character data efficiently so users can interact with all 8 characters without performance issues.\n75: \n76: **Business Value:** Enables FR-01 by providing the data persistence layer for character gallery functionality.\n77: \n78: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n79: \n80: Given application initializes\n81: When component mounts\n82: Then fetch all character data from local data source\n83: And cache character data for session duration\n84: And maintain data integrity across all operations\n85: \n86: Given user requests character information\n87: When character data is accessed\n88: Then return character object with all required properties\n89: And include character name, image, description metadata\n90: And ensure response time under 10ms\n91: \n92: Given data structure validation\n93: When character data is processed\n94: Then validate each character has required fields\n95: And ensure data types are consistent\n96: And handle missing or invalid data gracefully\n97: \n98: Given memory management requirements\n99: When application runs for extended sessions\n100: Then monitor character data memory usage\n101: And clean up unused character references\n102: And maintain performance under multiple operations\n103: \n104: Given security constraints\n105: When character data is processed\n106: Then sanitize data before display\n107: And validate data structure integrity\n108: And prevent XSS vulnerabilities in character content\n109: \n110: **Definition of Done:**\n111: - Character data source accessible and valid\n112: - Data caching mechanism implemented\n113: - Memory usage optimized\n114: - Input validation and sanitization complete\n115: - Error handling covers data failures\n116: - Performance targets met (<10ms access)\n117: - Security validation passes", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 117, "returned_lines": 117, "has_more": false, "eof_reached": true, "truncated": false}}}
