{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\artifacts\\outputs\\product-delivery\\user-stories\\epics\\EPIC-02.md", "content": "1: ---\n2: epic_id: EPIC-02\n3: epic_title: Real-time Search and Filter Engine\n4: session_id: product-delivery010307\n5: generated_at: 2026-07-03T16:35:00.000Z\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # EPIC-02: Real-time Search and Filter Engine Stories\n9: \n10: ## ST-03: Search Interface Components\n11: \n12: **Tag:** [FE] Frontend/Web  \n13: **Priority:** Must Have  \n14: **Source FRs:** FR-02  \n15: **Source NFRs:** NFR-03, NFR-07  \n16: **KPIs:** KPI-03  \n17: **Personas:** P-01, P-02\n18: \n19: **User Story:** As a beginner JavaScript student, I want to type in a search box and see instant character filtering so I can practice ES6+ array methods in real-time scenarios.\n20: \n21: **Business Value:** Instant character filtering demonstrates JavaScript ES6+ array methods and reactive data binding patterns in practical scenarios.\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n24: \n25: Given user views character gallery\n26: When search input component renders\n27: Then display search input field with appropriate placeholder\n28: And position search interface above character grid\n29: And ensure input field is keyboard accessible\n30: \n31: Given user types in search field\n32: When keyboard input occurs\n33: Then update character filter with each keystroke\n34: And maintain responsive typing experience\n35: And show real-time character count of results\n36: \n37: Given search input is empty\n38: When user clears search field\n39: Then display all characters in original grid\n40: And update result count to display all characters\n41: And maintain visual consistency with original state\n42: \n43: Given invalid search patterns\n44: When user enters special characters\n45: Then handle input gracefully without errors\n46: And filter based on valid text content only\n47: And maintain application stability\n48: \n49: Given search results are empty\n50: When no characters match search query\n51: Then display \"No results found\" message\n52: And provide option to clear search\n53: And maintain responsive layout\n54: \n55: Given API/network errors occur\n56: When search functionality fails\n57: Then display error state with retry option\n58: And maintain character grid visibility\n59: And log error for debugging purposes\n60: \n61: **Definition of Done:**\n62: - Search input component functional\n63: - Real-time filtering works per keystroke\n64: - Empty search shows all characters\n65: - No results state handled gracefully\n66: - Error states implemented\n67: - Accessibility standards met\n68: - Cross-browser compatibility verified\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## ST-04: Real-time Search Logic\n73: \n74: **Tag:** [BE] Backend/API  \n75: **Priority:** Must Have  \n76: **Source FRs:** FR-02  \n77: **Source NFRs:** NFR-07  \n78: **KPIs:** KPI-03  \n79: **Personas:** P-01, P-02\n80: \n81: **User Story:** As a web application, I need to process search queries efficiently so users can filter characters with <100ms response time and demonstrate performance optimization techniques.\n82: \n83: **Business Value:** Enables FR-02 by providing the filtering engine that meets real-time performance requirements for JavaScript learning scenarios.\n84: \n85: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n86: \n87: Given user enters search query\n88: When search input is processed\n89: Then filter character array using appropriate ES6+ methods\n90: And return matching characters within 100ms\n91: And maintain case-insensitive search capability\n92: \n93: Given character search algorithm\n94: When matching characters\n95: Then compare search terms against character names\n96: And include partial matches from character start\n97: And exclude already filtered out characters\n98: \n99: Given search performance requirements\n100: When processing large datasets", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 100, "returned_lines": 100, "has_more": true, "eof_reached": false, "truncated": false}}}
